               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        
                        Indenture between <persName>
                           <forename>Rolande</forename> 
                           <surname>Hill</surname>, citizen and mercer of <placeName role="person" key="place_100051">London</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
                        and <persName>Sir <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Pope</surname>, kt.</persName>, 
                        witnessing that whereas the late
                        <persName>
                           <forename>G<supplied>eorge</supplied>
                           </forename> 
                           <surname>N<supplied>evile</supplied>
                           </surname>
                        lord of B<supplied>ergevenny</supplied>
                        </persName>, 
                        by an indenture, dated 2nd Nov. 25 Hen. VIII, between him and
                        the said R. H. reciting that whereas the said Lord B. had received the rent
                        of £29 of the grant of <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">Fitz-James</surname>, Lord Chief Justice</persName>,
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Anthony</forename> 
                           <surname>Babyngton</surname>, kt.</persName>,
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Rouland</forename> 
                           <surname>Babyngton</surname>, gentleman</persName>, 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Whethalle</surname>
                        </persName> and
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Edmonde</forename> 
                           <surname>Toumer</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108296">Hythefelde</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
                        and now granted it to R. H., by this indenture R. H. grants it to
                        <persName>Sir <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Pope</surname>
                        </persName>, for £580. 
                        <origDate when="1541-05-06">6 May <supplied>1541.</supplied>
                        </origDate> 
                        R. H. is bound in 1000 marks to observe this. (Bond and indenture both signed by R. H.) 
                        Enrolled in Chancery on May 11th. </p>
                  </msItem>
